      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "Even at night, air temperatures were positive above 3000 m. <br/> In particular above approximately 2500 m and shady slopes: The early morning will see favourable conditions for a short time, but the danger of wet and gliding avalanches will increase later. <br/> <br/> As a consequence of warming and solar radiation, the natural activity of medium moist and wet avalanches will rapidly increase, in particular on very steep sunny slopes. This also applies at the base of rock walls, including on very steep shady slopes at intermediate altitudes. <br/> Especially on extremely steep slopes avalanches can release the wet old snow as well and reach large size in isolated cases. <br/> <br/> Backcountry tours and off-piste skiing should be started and concluded very early. <br/>",
